{
  "id": "4",
  "title": "4. Structured Output Integration",
  "type": "lab",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "# [4. Structured Output Integration]"
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "content": "Structured JSON & Response Verification Schema"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Integrating agents into software projects requires structured, predictable outputs instead of generic text. This module covers enforcing structured responses matching Pydantic classes (Python) and JSON Schema structures (Node.js)."
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Enforcing Response Schemas"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "By supplying a schema to response_schema (Python) or responseSchema (Node.js) inside LocalAgentConfig, the model is constrained to output structured JSON. We access the validated, formatted data using the structured_output() response handler."
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Python Structured Output Script"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "This script utilizes a Pydantic model to extract data points into a Python dictionary."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "import asyncio",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "from google.antigravity import Agent, LocalAgentConfig",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "import pydantic",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# Define the target schema structure using Pydantic",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "class SystemHealthReport(pydantic.BaseModel):",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "hostname: str",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "status: str",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "disk_utilization_pct: float",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "critical_warnings: list[str]",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "async def structured_output_run():",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "config = LocalAgentConfig(",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "response_schema=SystemHealthReport",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": ")",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "async with Agent(config) as agent:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "prompt = (",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "'Parse this status input: web-node-03 is running correctly. '",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "'Disk space utilization is currently at 78.4 percent. '",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "'Warnings: low_memory_warning detected.'",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": ")",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "response = await agent.chat(prompt)",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# Access the parsed JSON matching the Pydantic schema",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "data = await response.structured_output()",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "print('Parsed Python Dictionary:')",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "print(data)",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# Field verification",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "print(f'Host: {data.get(\"hostname\")}')",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "print(f'Disk utilization: {data.get(\"disk_utilization_pct\")}%')",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "if __name__ == '__main__':",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "asyncio.run(structured_output_run())",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Node.js Structured Output Script"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Below is the equivalent implementation in Node.js using JSON Schema to enforce structure."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "import { Agent, LocalAgentConfig } from '@google/antigravity';",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "async function runStructuredOutput() {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "// Define response validation schema using JSON Schema",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const reportSchema = {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "type: 'object',",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "properties: {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "hostname: { type: 'string' },",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "status: { type: 'string' },",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "disk_utilization_pct: { type: 'number' },",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "critical_warnings: {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "type: 'array',",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "items: { type: 'string' }",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "},",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "required: ['hostname', 'status', 'disk_utilization_pct', 'critical_warnings']",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "};",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const config = new LocalAgentConfig({",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "responseSchema: reportSchema",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "});",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const agent = new Agent(config);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "await agent.start();",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "try {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const prompt =",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "'Parse this status input: web-node-03 is running correctly. ' +",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "'Disk space utilization is currently at 78.4 percent. ' +",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "'Warnings: low_memory_warning detected.';",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const response = await agent.chat(prompt);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "// Access validated JSON payload",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "const data = await response.structured_output();",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "console.log('Parsed Javascript Object:');",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "console.log(data);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "console.log(`Host: ${data.hostname}`);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "console.log(`Disk utilization: ${data.disk_utilization_pct}%`);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "} finally {",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "await agent.stop();",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "runStructuredOutput().catch(console.error);",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> [!NOTE]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> If the model's output cannot be successfully parsed against the schema, response.structured_output() will return None (Python) or null (Node.js). Ensure your integrations validate outputs before passing data down the pipeline."
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Check Your Understanding"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Question 1: Which method is invoked to retrieve the parsed JSON payload matching the configured schema?"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- A) response.json()"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- B) response.structured_output()"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- C) response.to_dict()"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- D) response.get_schema_output()"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Feedback: Correct Answer: B. The structured_output() method parses, validates, and yields the matching JSON response structure."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Question 2: How do you register a validation schema in the Node.js SDK?"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- A) By passing a Pydantic class imported from Python."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- B) By writing a standard XML Schema document."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- C) By defining a JSON Schema object under the responseSchema configuration parameter."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "- D) By using a regular expression filter string."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Feedback: Correct Answer: C. In Node.js, the validation schema is registered as a standard JSON Schema object under the responseSchema parameter inside LocalAgentConfig."
    }
  ]
}